  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "We describe the generative model in Section 3.1, and the encoder-decoder in Section 3.2.",
    "For simplicity, we describe the model for the temporal conditioning setting, the adaptation for the generalisation from context setting is immediate.",
    "The core contribution of ENMA lies in its continuous autoregressive architecture, designed for modeling spatiotemporal dynamics.",
    "The generative model proceeds in two stages (5): it first extracts a spatio-temporal representation Z L DYN from the encoded trajectory Z 0:L-1 using a causal transformer, and then predicts the spatial distribution of the next time step via a tokenwise decoding mechanism.",
    "This distribution is estimated with a flow-matching component, with the help of a spatial transformer and a lightweight MLP, inspired by recent autoregressive models such as MAR (Li et al., 2024)."
  ],
